<h2 id="ΉνΑΈ╣ΕΊΧαΈΛΦ-Έ░σΈ▓Χ">ΉνΑΈ╣ΕΊΧαΈΛΦ Έ░σΈ▓Χ</h2>

<ul>
  <li><u>Recall recent situations that show favorable behaviors or actions</u>, especially involving course work, work experience, leadership, teamwork, initiative, planning, and customer service.</li>
  <li><u>Prepare short descriptions of each situation</u>; be ready to give details if asked.</li>
  <li>Be sure <u>each story has a beginning, middle, and an end</u>, i.e., be ready to describe the situation, including the task at hand, your action, and the outcome or result.</li>
  <li>Be sure the <u>outcome or result reflects positively on you</u> (even if the result itself was not favorable).</li>
  <li><u>Be honest.</u> DonέΑβt embellish or omit any part of the story. The interviewer will find out if your story is built on a weak foundation.</li>
  <li><u>Be specific.</u> DonέΑβt generalize about several events; give a detailed accounting of one event.</li>
  <li><u>Vary your examples</u>; donέΑβt take them all from just one area of your life.</li>
</ul>

